<br>
Before you choose a necro as your main, I'd suggest you look at the PoP end game and determine what you want past the 60's.  Necros used to be extremely group friendly, capable of soloing for everything they needed, and generally highly versatile through a host of abilities to support the DoTs and pets with which necros do damage.<br>
<br>
With PoP, everything has changed.  With recent nerfs, VI has essentially destroyed necromancer soloing, crowd control, and general versatility in the higher tier planes.  Summoning, root-immune/snare-immune mobs too high to be mezzed and feared by necros are becoming the NORM, rather than the exception, in the PoP tier 2/tier 3 planes.  This is getting ALOT of us frustrated to the highest degree, because without our versatility the necromancer is nothing but a weakened version of the mage, and if you're going to pick a necro, you should be prepared to deal with this.  Not a deterrent by any means, but anyone trying to choose between the two should realize that the necro from 1-60 is not the necro from 61-65, and that alot of information in this thread regarding necro versatility are not as good as they sound in practice, mostly due to hardcoded limitations on part of VI.<br>
<br>
<br>
