<br>
Second of all, it seems to me many of you missed the essence of my post.  Necros are not only about damage.  We are, and always were, powerful because of our versatile abilities.  THESE were nerfed in PoP, even if damage was not.  This is what most necros are complaining about, despite receiving quite good upgrades to damage (Neurotoxin 1.3k nuke, Saryn's Kiss 2k damage in 1 minute, Touch of Mujaki 830 lifetap w/3 second casting time).  Necros do NOT want to become crappier mages with root.  If that was what we wanted we would've all just rolled mages.  <br>
<br>
The complaint is not about damage.  It's about utility.  Necro utility has been diminished.  It's the &quot;versatility&quot; mages here often talk about when they are asked to define the difference between necros and mages.  When you talk about a necro, you don't say: &quot;he is a slower version of the mage&quot;, you say &quot;necromancers are a pet class with very good defensive and utility abilities aside from damage.&quot;  That definition is being phased out, not necro DPS.<br>
<br>
