<br>
I can't really comment on the higher end spell lineup since I don't have it.<br>
<br>
We have an undead Mez that's fast enough casting and last 30 seconds and works on up to level 59 undead. Are there level 59 and lower undead in PoP? Enough to make this a worthy spell?<br>
<br>
I've seen some PoV groups and I've seen a Shaman eat a fast 1k in damage from a resisted slow, same with Chanters. Group heal taps work nicely in this situation where one round of misplaced aggro can cause a LOT of healing to be required of the Cleric.<br>
<br>
With the changes to Mod rods, I'd also like to see a parse of damage throughout an entire evening. You know, when the Mage or Wizard has to stop casting and wait for mana to come back? (In the REALLY good groups where there's a fresh mob inc just as the last one is falling.)<br>
<br>
Necros can keep up their pace for QUITE a long time and give continued and consistant damage output. Kinda like a Rogue.<br>
<br>
I've seen some big pulls in the Factory where our Wizard said &quot;BURNING!&quot; and went into full blast mode and we put the trains down in record time. Our Wizard tries to keep himself at 50% mana or better at all times in case this is needed. <br>
<br>
Here's how I see the vision of our classes:<br>
<br>
Wizards are the masters of burst damage.<br>
<br>
Mages are somewhere in between burst damage and long term damage with the pets.<br>
<br>
Necros I would say have been envisioned as the Masters of the long haul damage with their mana regen and pets.<br>
<br>
With their nukes, lifetaps, Mind Wrack, Zevfeer's Theft of Vitae (Group Mana and health taps.) they can contribute QUITE a bit to a group over the course of an evening.<br>
